musb: host - suniv DMA fixes to musb_host_rx/urb-cleanup (PIO fallback + flush)

Two host-path fixes needed by the sunxi_dma backend, which (unlike inventra/ux500)
gates short/misaligned transfers to PIO and shares one FIFO datapath between PIO
and DMA via a global VEND0 BUS_SEL bit:

1) musb_host_rx(): when musb_rx_dma_in_inventra_cppi41() declines the RX DMA
   (channel_program returns 0 for a short transfer) the helper released
   hw_ep->rx_channel, but the caller's local `dma` still pointed at it, so the
   `if (!dma)` PIO block was skipped and the packet was dropped -> the AA session
   stalled after "Accessory linked". Refresh the local `dma` (now NULL) so RX
   falls through to PIO, mirroring the TX fallback.

2) musb_cleanup_urb(): on usb_kill_urb of a TX urb, musb_h_tx_flush_fifo() runs
   under musb->lock (IRQs off). If the RX video DMA left BUS_SEL=1 the TX FIFO is
   in DMA mode and FLUSHFIFO never empties it -> a 1s spin + "Could not flush host
   TX fifo" warning whose backtrace stalls the console and trips RT throttling
   (killing the AA read thread). Return the FIFO to PIO (VEND0=0) before the
   flush; the lock guarantees no DMA re-arms in between. Gated on
   CONFIG_USB_SUNXI_DMA so only suniv builds touch reg 0x43.

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>

--- a/drivers/usb/musb/musb_host.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/musb/musb_host.c
@@ -1924,8 +1924,14 @@
 			if (musb_rx_dma_in_inventra_cppi41(c, hw_ep, qh, urb,
 							   xfer_len, iso_err))
 				goto finish;
-			else
-				dev_err(musb->controller, "error: rx_dma failed\n");
+			/*
+			 * The DMA backend declined this RX (e.g. a short
+			 * transfer the sunxi engine rejects): the helper has
+			 * already released rx_channel, so drop our stale local
+			 * ref and fall through to the PIO path below instead of
+			 * losing the packet.  Mirrors the TX PIO fallback.
+			 */
+			dma = hw_ep->rx_channel;
 		}
 
 		if (!dma) {
@@ -2339,6 +2345,20 @@
 		if (is_dma_capable() && dma)
 			musb_platform_clear_ep_rxintr(musb, ep->epnum);
 	} else if (ep->epnum) {
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_USB_SUNXI_DMA)
+		/*
+		 * suniv MUSB shares one FIFO datapath between PIO and DMA,
+		 * gated by a global VEND0 BUS_SEL bit (reg 0x43). If the RX
+		 * video DMA left BUS_SEL=1, the TX FIFO is in DMA mode and
+		 * FLUSHFIFO can never empty it, so musb_h_tx_flush_fifo() spins
+		 * 1s and warns ("Could not flush host TX fifo: csr 21xx"), whose
+		 * backtrace print then stalls the console / RT thread. Return
+		 * the FIFO to PIO before flushing. We hold musb->lock (IRQs
+		 * off) so no DMA re-arms in between; the interrupted RX DMA is
+		 * re-requested by the core on its next poll.
+		 */
+		writeb(0, musb->mregs + 0x43);
+#endif
 		musb_h_tx_flush_fifo(ep);
 		csr = musb_readw(epio, MUSB_TXCSR);
 		csr &= ~(MUSB_TXCSR_AUTOSET
